metadata.name: INTERFERENCES #127
metadata.description:
INTERFERENCES is an abstract representation of the incredible collaboration between artists, collectors and developers on fxhash.

Each edition is composed of a multitude of lines representing each individual on the platform. The color of each line defines the role of each individual in this universe. Through their interactions, and the interferences they produce, each line participates in the creation of a common work.

Happy birthday fxhash! And congratulations to all those who work for its success.

Primary sales are donated to the Processing Foundation

[TOUCHSCREEN]
* Double Tap to save the current image

[KEYBOARD]
* Press [S] to save the current image
* Press [1] to save a 1500x2000 pixels PNG
* Press [2] to save a 3000x4000 pixels PNG
* Press [3] to save a 6000x8000 pixels PNG
* Press [0] to save 3 individual SVG for each color set of lines + the background image PNG
* Press [9] to save a grouped SVG of all the lines + the background image PNG

Artist: Estienne
Nov. 2022
NFT License 2.0

Credits to Piter Pasma (@piterpasma) for the Reumann-Witkam line simplification algorithm used in this generator

metadata.description:
Ocean is my second long-form generative work continuing my exploration of creating visual designs with polygons. As found with the name, Ocean, this piece is inspired by patterns of ocean waves, storms, typhoons, and urchins. Ocean is composed of six layout variations and four color palettes with a few singular inspirations.

metadata.name: Concrete #369
metadata.description:
640 unique sketches of imaginary walls, inspired by the work of Norwegian architect Erling Viksjø (1910–1971) and his artist collaborators. Viksjø designed the Government Quarter in Oslo and invited artists from different disciplines to help design the facades and interiors of the buildings.

Viksjø’s aim was to “soften” modernist architecture. He invented «Natural Concrete», a type of concrete that deliberately exposes the mixed-in stones on its surface to give it warmth and a human touch. In my work, I have similar ambitions—using code instead of concrete.

The different styles of the piece are inspired by, and dedicated to some of the artists who worked together with Viksjø: Jakob Weidemann (~2%), Carl Nesjar (~18%), Odd Tandberg (~30%), and Tore Haaland (~50%).

In live mode, press ‘S’ to save an image at current resolution or ‘P’ to save a high-resolution file at 6000×6000px (this might take a while depending on your hardware).

Original artwork by Andreas Rau · Made with p5.js & glsl · Oslo, 2021

metadata.name: Magic Board #128
metadata.description:
When the ratio of two quantities is equal to the ratio of their sum to the larger quantity, there is a golden ratio in geometric patterns, and this property can create different geometric shapes.
The points are all randomly placed in each design, and the placement of these shapes together creates the impression of a geometric pattern based on random processing.
There is no end to these geometric patterns.
press 's' to save original size

The orange and dark blue green colors in this work of art are trying to express themselves and they are fighting each other for this
